<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE PRIORITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California state legislators' recent salary increase from $52,000 to $72,000 
(38.5%) makes them the highest paid state legislators in the country. However, 
in the amount of money we spend on education, our ranking is closer to the 
bottom than the top.We rank 41st in the nation on a per-pupil expenditure of 
$4,621, which is considerably below the national average of $5,604. There are 
only nine states that spend less per pupil than we do. 
</P>
<P>
 I dare say our society would be much better served if the exact opposite were 
true: That we were first in the nation on educational expenditures, and that 
our legislators' salaries were ranked 41st. It's obvious that there is 
something terribly wrong with our priorities. 
</P>
<P>
 SONIA APPELL 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
