<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: MARK OZUR SELECTED AS NEW PRESIDENT OF DIGITAL SOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Digital Sound Corp. announced the appointment of Mark Ozur as president and 
chief executive, succeeding Robert T. Knight, who has been elected chairman of 
the firm. Knight succeeds J. David Hann, 62, who will remain on the board of 
the Carpinteria-based manufacturer of high-capacity network-based message 
processing systems.Ozur, 38, was previously executive vice president and 
general manager and joined Digital in May, 1993. Before that, he was vice 
president of engineering at Precision Visuals Inc. in Boulder, Colo. Knight, 
57, who became president and CEO in 1991, was previously vice chairman of the 
firm. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jeffrey L. Newman has joined First Interstate Bank of California's Trust and 
Private Services Group as executive vice president, managing director of First 
Interstate Portfolio Lending Services Inc. Newman is responsible for 
supervising the division's 22 professionals and overseeing all of its 
securities lending activities. Previously, Newman worked for Bank of New York, 
where he was responsible for the securities lending division. 
</P>
<P>
 * Donald L. Harrill has been elected senior vice president-vacation ownership 
operations of Hilton Hotels Corp. and chief executive of Hilton Grand Vacations 
Co. Hilton also announced the election of Jim Abrahamson a senior vice 
president-franchising and select hotels. Both appointments are effective Jan. 
1. Harrill, 44, will be responsible for day-to-day operations of Hilton Grand 
Vacations Co., a joint venture of Hilton Resorts Co., a Hilton subsidiary, and 
Grand Vacations Ltd. He was previously executive vice president-Hilton Inns 
Inc. and senior vice president-franchising Hilton Hotels. Abrahamson, 39, was 
most recently senior vice president-select hotels, overseeing operating of 
Hilton Suites, Hilton Garden Inns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122694-0033 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111482 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 26, 1994, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 4; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
