COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MOORPARK; MEDICAL CLINIC TO OPEN TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 County officials Tuesday will officially open Moorpark's new medical clinic, 
though its first patients will not be seen until next month. 
</P>
<P>
 The new clinic will replace a dilapidated facility on High Street that was 
closed 14 months ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Since then, Moorpark area residents who receive Medi-Cal or who lack health 
insurance have had to go to Simi Valley for subsidized care. Officials estimate 
that the Simi Valley clinic has treated 700 to 800 Moorpark residents this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 The new clinic, at 6559 Princeton Ave. near Moorpark College, will include 
examining rooms, a records room and a reception area. It will open for patients 
Jan. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 The county has spent about $220,000 renovating the privately owned building. 
Rent for the 4,400-square-foot storefront is $5,000 a month, Health Care Agency 
officials said. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
