<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOMINATIONS SOUGHT FOR WOMEN'S AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Commission for Women is accepting nominations for its 12th 
and final annual Salute to Women of Achievement Awards. 
</P>
<P>
 The nomination deadline is Jan. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 A dozen women will receive awards in 11 categories: arts, business, community 
service, education, entrepreneur, legal, media, public service, science/health, 
sports and outstanding young women. Two women will receive community service 
awards. 
</P>
<P>
 Winners will be announced during a banquet in Camarillo on March 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said the awards will be discontinued after the banquet so that the 
commission can better address "the barriers that hinder many women from 
becoming economically self-sufficient." 
</P>
<P>
 Nomination forms, invitations to the banquet and additional information can be 
obtained by calling Loma Siegel at 388-9587 or Celeste Weingardt at 658-1351. 
The event is co-sponsored by The Zonta Club of Ventura County and the B'hais. 
PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
