<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; CRASH KILLS DRIVER, INJURES PASSENGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old from Santa Paula died late Christmas Eve after her car spun out 
on rain-slicked California 126, veered onto the dirt shoulder and struck a 
tree, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Marisol Rodriguez was driving east on California 126 near Briggs Road with her 
21-year-old sister Maribell about 3:35 p.m. Saturday when she lost control of 
her car and crashed.No other vehicles were involved in the accident, California 
Highway Patrol officers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Marisol Rodriguez nor her sister were wearing seat belts, authorities 
said, and emergency equipment was needed to remove them from the wreckage. 
</P>
<P>
 Both sisters suffered internal injuries and were taken to Santa Paula 
Hospital. Marisol Rodriguez was transferred later to Ventura County Medical 
Center, where she was pronounced dead about 9 p.m. Saturday, said Dale Zentzis 
of the Ventura County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the past five years, 29 people have died along the winding stretch of 
California 126 between Ventura and the Los Angeles County line east of 
Fillmore. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
