<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: CAMARILLO; MALATHION SPRAYING SCHEDULED TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Weather permitting, the sixth aerial spraying of malathion will be conducted 
Tuesday over a 16-square-mile section of eastern Camarillo, state and federal 
agriculture officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The three helicopters are scheduled to lift off from Camarillo Airport at 10 
p.m. for what is expected to be a four-hour mission, said Larry Hawkins, a 
spokesman for the Cooperative Medfly Project. 
</P>
<P>
 Beginning next month, Hawkins said, the helicopters will resume their normal 9 
p.m. takeoff time. Agriculture officials pushed back the departure time one 
hour this month to accommodate late-night holiday shoppers. J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
