<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN WHO FLED ACCIDENT SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man driving east on Saticoy Street crossed the double yellow line and 
collided head-on with a westbound car Saturday night, seriously injuring one 
woman before fleeing the accident on foot, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not identified a suspect in the 9:30 p.m. incident, said Officer 
John Teetor of the Los Angeles Police Department's Valley Traffic Division. The 
car was abandoned at the accident site near Saticoy Street and Beck Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The injured woman, identified as Maria Hernandez, was rushed to Holy Cross 
Medical Center with multiple fractures and lacerations, Teetor said. Five 
others riding in the car with Hernandez, whose residence is not known, were 
treated for minor injuries at the scene, Teetor said. 
</P>
