<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS YEAR AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RAY DELGADO , Thumbnail sketches of the 1995 regional economies, based on 
the 1995-96 Economic Forecast & Industry Outlook for California and the Los 
Angeles Five-County Area, as compiled by the Los Angeles County Economic 
Development Corp.: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Foggy Days Are Here: The outlook for the county is clouded by its bankruptcy 
filing, which will delay public works projects, among other things.But the 
county will record an overall increase of 17,000 jobs and unemployment will 
remain low, dipping to 5.4% from 5.9%, despite the loss of another 6,000 
aerospace jobs. Big job gains are forecast for accountants, financial 
specialists, insurers and real estate brokers. Both total personal income and 
retail sales in 1995 will increase by roughly 6%, raising the figures to $70.6 
billion and $18.7 billion, respectively. Housing permits will fall 15% next 
year, however, from 11,670 this year to 10,000 in 1995. RAY DELGADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122694-0133 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111582 </DOCID>
