</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS YEAR AHEAD: VENTURA COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RAY DELGADO , Thumbnail sketches of the 1995 regional economies, based on 
the 1995-96 Economic Forecast & Industry Outlook for California and the Los 
Angeles Five-County Area, as compiled by the Los Angeles County Economic 
Development Corp.: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Not Much in the Way of Jobs: Sluggish employment growth will continue in 1995 
as only 3,000 new non-farm jobs are expected in a county with an employment 
base of more than 230,000 people.However, the jobless rate will decline for the 
second straight year, to 7.9% from 8.2%. Personal income is expected to rise by 
about $1 billion to $17.2 billion, while retail sales are expected to increase 
by $200 million to $4.3 billion. Only 200 new housing requests are expected, 
bringing the total to 2,500. RAY DELGADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122694-0134 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 111583 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 26, 1994, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
