<TEXT>
<P>
 Machine Tool Orders Up: Orders for American-made machine tools rose 2.9% in 
November, an industry group said in a report that suggested growing demand for 
manufactured goods.The Assn. for Manufacturing Technology reported that machine 
tool orders totaled $370.25 million in November, up from $359.80 million in 
October. Orders were up 59.38% over November, 1993. The latest results contrast 
with October, when orders plunged 30% to $359.80 million from a September peak 
of $514.55 million. Total machine tool orders for the first 11 months of the 
year rose 37.42% to $4.07 billion. 
</P>
