</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Farmers Insurance Stunned by Size of Award: Company officials said they will 
immediately appeal the decision by a jury in Portland, Ore., to award $38.5 
million to a fired Farmers Insurance Co. district manager."This jury award is 
absolutely outrageous" and "wholly without foundation," said Daryl Hubard, 
president of Farmers Insurance Co. of Oregon. The Multnomah County jury reached 
its decision after a complicated eight-week trial. The company fired Darrell 
Bennett, 45, in August and demanded all his records and paperwork. Bennett 
claimed he had received verbal assurances that Farmers would fire him only in a 
case of fraud or theft. 
</P>
