<TEXT>
<P>
 Capital Investment Exceeds Forecast: The country's business sector expects 
that the government will substantially exceed its forecast for business 
investment growth of 14.5% in the year ending June 30.A survey by the Business 
Council of Australia, which covers the nation's major companies, said 
three-fifths of respondents now expect capital expenditure to grow by more than 
20%. The council's ninth half-yearly survey of current business conditions 
indicates that most businesses believe strong economic growth will continue. 
The economy grew 6.4% in the year ended Sept. 30, a nine-year high. However, 
respondents said they expect inflation will rise slightly over the next five 
years. 
</P>
